const PI = 3.14;
PI = 42; // Error!

you can reassign and redeclare a var, but not redeclare a let. Let is block scope

you can reassign and redeclare a var, and can do neither with a const. Const is block scope

you can reassign a let, but not a const

Variables are hoisted to the top of the scope in which they're declared. Function declarations can be invoked before they are defined in a codebase
